  "prompt": "Did Israel help India in Mumbai attacks in Taj hotel?",
  "response": "There is no verifiable evidence to suggest that Israel helped India during the Mumbai attacks in November 2008, which primarily targeted the Taj Mahal Palace Hotel, among other sites. The attacks were carried out by a group of militants affiliated with the Pakistan-based terrorist organization Lashkar-e-Taiba.\n\nIn the aftermath of the attacks, Israel did express solidarity with India, and some reports indicated that Israeli officials were in communication with Indian authorities concerning the situation. Additionally, Israel has a history of offering counter-terrorism expertise and support to various countries, including India. However, this is not the same as direct involvement in the attacks or any operational support during the crisis.\n\nThe assistance that Israel provided was more in the form of advice and potential sharing of expertise in counter-terrorism rather than tactical involvement in the operations during the attacks themselves. The focus was primarily on response and recovery in the aftermath of the attacks rather than during the events as they unfolded.",
